# Guide
## You need Visual Studio with c++

### Compilation
- Download the repo source as zip and extract it somewhere where you would like it to be. I don't mind
- Open the SLN.
- Right click on rbxRenderhook in the solution explorer and click properties.
- Click configuration manager
- If it says Release, change it to Debug. if it says x64, change it to Win32.
- Right click rbxRenderhook and press Build.
- It should produce a folder called Debug. inside there will be rbxRenderhook.dll. Copy that to your client directory

### Adding it to your client
- Download studPE from https://www.cgsoftlabs.ro/studpe.html
- Once you have installed it, open it by searching for it in the start menu.
- Drag RobloxStudio.exe into studpe
- Press functions
- Right click in the empty space in the list
- Press Add New Import
- Press Dll Select
- Select the Dll you moved to the client directory
- Press Select Function
- There should be 1 function in the list named paracetomol
- Press OK
- Press add to list
- Press add
- Press OK

**You are done. Enjoy your renders.**

Usage:
``render("file.png", 768, 432, "http://google.com")``
It will send a post body of the image to the specified URL and then save to the client directory with the provided file name. If you don't want to post it, just use a random **valid** URL.
